import os
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from tqdm import tqdm
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error
from arch import arch_model
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')


PARQUET_PATH = "/Users/shiyuchen/Downloads/DATA3888_Optiver_9_GroupCode/LSTM/New_60s_bucket.parquet"
WINDOW = 30           
ROLL_STEP = 30        
SCALE_FACTOR = 1e4    
target_col = "realized_volatility"


df = pd.read_parquet(PARQUET_PATH)
df["date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["date"])
df["day_of_week"] = df["date"].dt.dayofweek + 1
df["week"] = df["date"].dt.isocalendar().week


if "day" not in df.columns:
    df["day"] = df["date"].dt.normalize()
if "minute_idx" not in df.columns:
    df.sort_values(["stock_id", "date", "time_id", "bucket_start"], inplace=True)
    df["minute_idx"] = df.groupby(["stock_id", "day"]).cumcount()

def median_absolute_error(t, p):
    return np.median(np.abs(t - p))

def mape(t, p):
    t = np.clip(t, 1e-8, None)
    return np.mean(np.abs((t - p) / t)) * 100

def smape(t, p):
    denom = np.clip(np.abs(t) + np.abs(p), 1e-8, None)
    return np.mean(2 * np.abs(p - t) / denom) * 100

def qlike(t, p):
    t = np.clip(t, 1e-8, None)
    p = np.clip(p, 1e-8, None)
    return np.mean(np.log(p) + t / p)

def select_best_egarch_params(y_data, max_p=3, max_o=2, max_q=3, dist_list=['Normal', 't']):
    """
    使用AIC准则选择最优EGARCH参数
    """
    best_aic = np.inf
    best_params = None
    best_model = None
    
    eps = 1e-12
    y_log = np.log(y_data + eps)
    y_log_centered = y_log - y_log.mean()
    
    
    for p in range(1, max_p + 1):
        for o in range(1, max_o + 1):
            for q in range(1, max_q + 1):
                for dist in dist_list:
                    try:
                        model = arch_model(
                            y_log_centered,
                            mean="Constant",
                            vol="EGARCH",
                            p=p,
                            o=o,
                            q=q,
                            dist=dist,
                            rescale=False
                        )
                        fit = model.fit(disp="off", show_warning=False)
                        
                        if fit.converged:
                            aic = fit.aic
                            if aic < best_aic:
                                best_aic = aic
                                best_params = {'p': p, 'o': o, 'q': q, 'dist': dist}
                                best_model = fit
                    except:
                        continue
    
    return best_params, best_model, best_aic


METRICS_CSV = "EGARCH_new_weekly_metrics.csv"
PRED_CSV = "EGARCH_pred_true_records.csv"
for f in (METRICS_CSV, PRED_CSV):
    if os.path.exists(f):
        os.remove(f)

first_write, pred_first_write = True, True


stock_best_params = {}


for sid in tqdm(sorted(df["stock_id"].unique()), desc="Processing stock"):
    
    sub_s = df[df["stock_id"] == sid].copy()
    stock_true_all, stock_pred_all = [], []
    
    
    stock_params = None
    
    for wk in sorted(sub_s["week"].unique()):
        wk_df = sub_s[sub_s["week"] == wk]
        fri_df = wk_df[wk_df.day_of_week == 5].sort_values("minute_idx")
        
        if fri_df.empty or len(fri_df) <= WINDOW:
            continue
        
        rows_for_csv = [
            {
                "stock_id": int(sid),
                "week": int(wk),
                "day_of_week": 5,
                "bucket": int(row["minute_idx"]),
                "true": row[target_col],
                "pred": np.nan,
            }
            for _, row in fri_df.iterrows()
        ]
        
        last_window_idx = -1
        egarch_fit = None
        
        for i in range(WINDOW, len(fri_df)):
            y_hist = fri_df.iloc[i - WINDOW : i][target_col].values
            y_hist_scaled = y_hist * SCALE_FACTOR
            
            
            current_window_idx = (i - WINDOW) // ROLL_STEP
            refit_needed = (current_window_idx != last_window_idx)
            
            if refit_needed:
                
                if stock_params is None and len(y_hist_scaled) >= 30:
                    
                    stock_params, _, best_aic = select_best_egarch_params(
                        y_hist_scaled, 
                        max_p=3, 
                        max_o=2, 
                        max_q=3, 
                        dist_list=['normal', 't', 'skewt']
                    )
                    
                    if stock_params is not None:
                        stock_best_params[sid] = stock_params
                    
                    else:
                        
                        stock_params = {'p': 1, 'o': 1, 'q': 1, 'dist': 'skewt'}
                
                
                if stock_params is not None:
                    eps = 1e-12
                    y_log = np.log(y_hist_scaled + eps)
                    y_log_centered = y_log - y_log.mean()
                    
                    egarch_fit = None
                    if len(y_log_centered) >= 30:
                        try:
                            egarch_fit = arch_model(
                                y_log_centered,
                                mean="Constant",
                                vol="EGARCH",
                                p=stock_params['p'],
                                o=stock_params['o'],
                                q=stock_params['q'],
                                dist=stock_params['dist'],
                                rescale=False,
                            ).fit(disp="off", show_warning=False)
                            
                            if not egarch_fit.converged:
                                egarch_fit = None
                        except Exception as e:
                            egarch_fit = None
                
                last_window_idx = current_window_idx
            
            
            if egarch_fit is not None:
                try:
                    forecast = egarch_fit.forecast(horizon=1)
                    cond_var = forecast.variance.iloc[-1, 0]
                    
                    hist_mean = np.mean(y_hist)
                    hist_std = np.std(y_hist)
                    
                    if hist_std > 0:
                        cond_std = np.sqrt(cond_var)
                        log_std = np.std(np.log(y_hist_scaled + 1e-12) - np.log(y_hist_scaled + 1e-12).mean())
                        
                        if log_std > 0:
                            vol_factor = cond_std / log_std
                            vol_factor = np.clip(vol_factor, 0.5, 2.0)
                        else:
                            vol_factor = 1.0
                        
                        y_hat = hist_mean * vol_factor
                    else:
                        y_hat = hist_mean
                    
                except Exception:
                    y_hat = np.mean(y_hist)
            else:
                y_hat = np.mean(y_hist)
            
            
            upper_bound = np.percentile(y_hist, 95) * 1.5
            lower_bound = np.percentile(y_hist, 5) * 0.5
            y_hat = np.clip(y_hat, lower_bound, upper_bound)
            
            if np.isnan(y_hat):
                y_hat = np.mean(y_hist)
            
            stock_true_all.append(fri_df.iloc[i][target_col])
            stock_pred_all.append(y_hat)
            rows_for_csv[i]["pred"] = y_hat
        
        
        if rows_for_csv and not all(np.isnan(row["pred"]) for row in rows_for_csv):
            valid_rows = [r for r in rows_for_csv if not np.isnan(r["pred"])]
            y_t = np.array([r["true"] for r in valid_rows])
            y_p = np.array([r["pred"] for r in valid_rows])
            
            if stock_params is not None:
                model_desc = f"EGARCH({stock_params['p']},{stock_params['o']},{stock_params['q']},{stock_params['dist']})"
            else:
                model_desc = "EGARCH(NA)"
            
            metrics_row = {
                "stock": int(sid),
                "week": int(wk),
                "model": model_desc,
                "RMSE": np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_t, y_p)),
                "MAE": mean_absolute_error(y_t, y_p),
                "MedAE": median_absolute_error(y_t, y_p),
                "MAPE(%)": mape(y_t, y_p),
                "SMAPE(%)": smape(y_t, y_p),
                "QLIKE": qlike(y_t, y_p),
            }
            
            pd.DataFrame([metrics_row]).to_csv(
                METRICS_CSV,
                mode="w" if first_write else "a",
                header=first_write,
                index=False,
            )
            first_write = False
            
            pd.DataFrame(rows_for_csv).to_csv(
                PRED_CSV,
                mode="w" if pred_first_write else "a",
                header=pred_first_write,
                index=False,
            )
            pred_first_write = False
    
    
    if stock_true_all:
        y_true_array = np.array(stock_true_all)
        y_pred_array = np.array(stock_pred_all)
        
        mae_val = mean_absolute_error(y_true_array, y_pred_array)
        rmse_val = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true_array, y_pred_array))
        
        print(f"\nStock {sid} - MAE: {mae_val:.6f}, RMSE: {rmse_val:.6f}")
        print(f"  True: mean={np.mean(y_true_array):.6f}, std={np.std(y_true_array):.6f}")
        print(f"  Pred: mean={np.mean(y_pred_array):.6f}, std={np.std(y_pred_array):.6f}")
        
        
        idx = np.arange(len(stock_true_all))
        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 3))
        plt.plot(idx, stock_true_all, label="True", alpha=0.7)
        plt.plot(idx, stock_pred_all, label="Pred", alpha=0.7)
        
        if sid in stock_best_params:
            params = stock_best_params[sid]
            title = f"Stock {int(sid)} – EGARCH({params['p']},{params['o']},{params['q']}) {params['dist']}"
        else:
            title = f"Stock {int(sid)} – EGARCH"
        
        plt.title(title)
        plt.xlabel("Sequential index")
        plt.ylabel("Realized volatility")
        plt.legend()
        plt.tight_layout()
        plt.show()
